What’s actually “holding” (grounded view)

Across change, systems keep identity through invariants like:
	•	continuity of pattern (the shape of behavior, not the parts)
	•	memory / history (what has been carried forward)
	•	constraints (what can and cannot change)
	•	relations (how parts connect, not just what they are)

That’s why a person:
	•	changes cells
	•	changes beliefs
	•	changes environment

…and still feels like “the same someone.”

